@startuml
' ITIL/ITSM-compliant Incident Management workflow for Jira Service Management
skinparam activityStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

title Jira Service Management - Incident Management (ITIL/ITSM)

start

fork
:Service end user reports issue;
  note right
    External user submits request
    via portal/chat/email.
  end note
fork again
:Monitoring system generates alert;
  note right
    Automated detection of incidents
    (e.g., availability/health checks).
  end note
fork again
:Internal IT member reports incident;
  note right
    Issues found during routine work
    or internal reviews.
  end note
end fork

:Service project agent logs incident in service project;
:Link related reports to the same incident;
:Record timestamp, reporter, and unique incident ID;

:Categorize incident with appropriate labels;
  note right
    Categories used for reporting
    and post-incident review inputs.
  end note

:Prioritize based on impact and urgency;
  note right
    Priority drives SLA targets
    and assignment order.
  end note

:Diagnose incident, affected services, and possible solutions;
:Communicate with reporters during diagnosis;

if (Escalation needed?
Complex/major impact?) then (Yes)
  :Escalate to 2nd-line support reps;
  :2nd-line investigates and works on affected systems;
endif

:Restore service / implement resolution;
:Verify fix is successful;
if (Resolution successful?) then (Yes)
  :Document resolution for future reference;
else (No)
  :Return to diagnosis for further investigation;
  --> Diagnose incident, affected services, and possible solutions;
endif

:Service project automatically closes incident;

stop
@enduml
